The paper discusses the construction of a knowledge graph for toxicological effect and risk assessment, which involves data integration and interoperability. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the development of predictive models, databases (cs.DB) for data management, machine learning (cs.LG) for data analysis, civil engineering (cs.CE) for risk assessment, and cybernetics (cs.CY) for the study of complex systems.
